Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Only 63 Acres Left! (Tracts 1, 3-B, 5)
Opportunity for a multi-use planned development
Across from Sedgefield Country Club (Home of the Wyndham Championship)
Adjacent to affluent communities of Adams Farm, Sedgefield & Grandover

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Its location near the new Greensboro urban loop (I-73) and Gate City Boulevard (Jamestown Bypass) creates tremendous potential for a multi-use planned development.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The Pilot at Sedgefield, previously the headquarters for Pilot Life Insurance Company, is a 131-acre campus with six entitled tracts of land available for development. Currently 63 acres left (Tracts 1, 3-B, 5). Potential uses for the project include single-family, multi-family residential, hotel/hospitality, retail or corporate headquarters. Tract 3-A includes six existing office buildings (five interconnected) totaling 222,000 SF that can remain or be removed. *The original buildings (ca. 1927) can be restored and used as an amenity for the entire development, or all of the buildings can be demolished.​

Common.Brochures.Common.BrochureName: Five Star Farms OM v7 EMAIL.pdf

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Excellent location in North Greensboro near I-840 and US-220 interchange. Site is located at the intersection of Horsepen Creek Rd and Jessup Grove Rd.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE|Triad is pleased to exclusively offer for sale Five Star Farms, a mixed-use development site located in north Greensboro near the interchange of US-220 (Battleground Ave) and I-840 (Greensboro Urban Loop). The site consists of 11 parcels of land totaling 115.23± acres and is located near several commercial shopping centers, schools, parks and recreation centers. The site is ideal for mixed-use (multifamily and commercial office/retail).

DESIRABLE LOCATION: Surrounded by several affluent high-income neighborhoods, retail shopping centers, office developments, private schools, recreational parks, and retirement communities with strong demographics.

ACCESS & INFRASTRUCTURE: In-place infrastructure includes public water/sewer and access from Jessup Grove Rd and Four Farms Rd. Greensboro Urban Loop (estimated completion November 2022) likely to increase access.

WELL POISED FOR FUTURE DEVELOPMENT: Site is surrounded by multiple land uses making it versatile for future development.  Potential to rezone for mixed-use development (retail/office, high density multi-family, moderate density multi-family, and residential).  Potential to rezone for specialty use zoning (master planned community and/or specialty use, retirement community, private school or health care related use).

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Five Star Farms - Land Development Opportunity
